{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "The NEMO 3 experiment searches for neutrinoless double beta decay and makes precision measurements of twoneutrino double beta decay in seven isotopes. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The latest two-neutrino half-life results are presented, together with the limits on neutrinoless half-lives and the corresponding effective Majorana neutrino masses. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Also given are the limits obtained on neutrinoless double beta decay mediated by R p -violating SUSY, right-hand currents and different Majoron emission modes.",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "INTRODUCTION",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Neutrinoless double beta decay (0\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 ) is a process in which two neutrons in a nucleus undergo simultaneous beta decays with the emission of two electrons. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "It violates lepton number and is therefore forbidden in the Standard Model. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The observation of neutrinoless double beta decay would prove that neutrinos are Majorana particles and would provide access to their absolute mass scale.",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The half-life of 0\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 is given by:",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "where M 0\u03bd (A, Z) is the nuclear matrix element (NME) and G 0\u03bd (Q, Z) is a known phase space factor that depends on the transition energy (Q-value) of the process. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The effective Majorana neutrino mass, m \u03b2 \u03b2 , is a sum over the mass eigenstates, weighted by the squared elements, U 2 ei , of the PMNS neutrino mixing matrix:",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "In addition to light Majorana neutrino exchange (described by (1)), 0\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 decay could be mediated by other physics mechanisms such as a right-hand current admixture in the Lagrangian, Majoron emission or supersymmetric particle exchange. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Measuring the energy spectrum and topology of the final state electrons could allow to distinguish between these underlying mechanisms.",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "NEMO 3 [1] (Neutrino Ettore Majorana Observatory) has been taking data since 2003 at the Modane Underground Laboratory in France. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 7,
                    "end": 10,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 7,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "NEMO 3",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The experiment is dedicated to searching for 0\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 decay and making precise lifetime measurements of 2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 decay in seven isotopes. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The main isotopes used for the 0\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 search are 7 kg of 100 Mo and 1 kg of 82 Se. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "There are smaller amounts of 116 Cd, 130 Te, 150 Nd, 96 Zr and 48 Ca for 2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 studies, and natural Te and Cu for background measurements. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "NEMO 3 employs an experimental technique of calorimetry and tracking, in order to detect the two final state electrons. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 7,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "NEMO 3",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The detector is cylindrical and is radially segmented into 20 equal sectors, each housing a thin source foil placed in the middle of a tracking volume, which is surrounded by the calorimeter. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The tracker consists of 6180 drift cells operated in Geiger mode. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The calorimeter walls are made up of 1940 plastic scintillator blocks coupled to low-radioactivity PMTs. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "They achieve energy resolution in the range 14%-17% FWHM for 1 MeV electrons and timing resolution of 250 ps. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "A solenoid magnetic field of 25 G is applied to provide charge identification. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The whole detector is enclosed in a radon-free air tent, and covered by two levels of external radiation shielding.",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The NEMO 3 detector measures the individual particle trajectories and energies, thus reconstructing the final state topology and kinematics of the events. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 9,
                    "end": 11,
                    "type": "version",
                    "rawForm": "3",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "#software-simple-s2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Through particle identification of e \u2212 , e + , \u03b1 and \u03b3 it achieves excellent background suppression, which is further enhanced by the time-of-flight measurement used to reject external particles crossing the detector.",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Double beta decay events are selected by requiring two tracks with a negative curvature, originating from a common vertex in the source foil and associated to isolated scintillator energy deposits. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The timing of the calorimeter hits is required to agree with the time-offlight hypothesis of two electrons emitted from the foil at the same time. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The remaining backgrounds in the two-electron signal sample are estimated by looking at control channels. ",
            "section": "THE NEMO 3 EXPERIMENT",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 RESULTS",
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Two-neutrino double beta decay (2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 ) is a Standard Model weak interaction process occurring in nuclei for which beta decay is energetically forbidden or strongly suppressed. ",
            "section": "2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The importance of understanding the 2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 process is because it forms the irreducible background to 0\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 decay. ",
            "section": "2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "In addition, precise measurements of its half-life and event kinematics are used to constrain the nuclear models used to calculate the neutrinoless NME.",
            "section": "2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The NEMO 3 experiment has been performing highstatistics measurements of 2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 decay in its seven isotopes. ",
            "section": "2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 11,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "NEMO 3",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Figures 1 and 2 show the recent preliminary results for the two-electron energy sum distributions obtained from 150 Nd and 96 Zr, respectively. ",
            "section": "2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 15,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_0",
                    "text": "Figures 1 and 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Table 1 summarises the current half-life measurements, along with the isotope characteristics and the signal-to-background ratios (S/B), obtained from all isotopes. ",
            "section": "2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 4,
