                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The 0\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 analysis of 100 Mo and 82 Se has now been blinded. ",
            "section": "Light neutrino exchange",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 33,
                    "end": 35,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "text": "82"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The projected half-life sensitivities when unblinded in 2010 are 2 \u00d7 10 24 years for 100 Mo and 8 \u00d7 10 23 years for 82 Se, leading to neutrino mass reaches of 0.3 \u2212 0.7 eV and 0.6 \u2212 1.1 eV, respectively.",
            "section": "Light neutrino exchange",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "SUSY particle exchange",
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "Neutrinoless double beta decay could be mediated by the exchange of superparticles in R p -violating SUSY [10]. ",
            "section": "SUSY particle exchange",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 106,
                    "end": 110,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[10]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The half-life of this process is inversely proportional to the SUSY lepton-number violating parameter \u03b7 11 (q)LR , which is related to the sum of R p -  ",
            "section": "SUSY particle exchange",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 6,
