        {
            "text": "Other exotic mechanisms",
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "Other exotic mechanisms such as right-hand (V + A) currents and Majoron emission could also contribute to 0\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 decay. ",
            "section": "Other exotic mechanisms",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "They would lead to a distortion of the shape of the two-electron energy sum distribution. ",
            "section": "Other exotic mechanisms",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "A maximum likelihood analysis of the deviation of the energy shape from the calculated 2\u03bd\u03b2 \u03b2 shape was performed [11]. ",
            "section": "Other exotic mechanisms",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 7,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 113,
                    "end": 117,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "[11]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The resulting limits on the half-lives and couplings for (V + A) currents and different Majoron spectral indices n are shown in Table 3.",
